                            <comment id="14167683" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 22:27:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch decouples the REST authentication from underlying HBase/Hadoop authentication.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167689" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 22:31:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is another one for you &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jxiang&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jxiang&quot;&gt;Jimmy Xiang&lt;/a&gt; to comment &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167737" author="apurtell" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 23:06:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If doing it this way I think we should default the REST auth mode to the HBase auth setting if a specific REST authentication mode isn&apos;t specified in the configuration. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current patch is ok for 0.98 and branch-1 but we might want to do differently in master. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167769" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 23:25:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are subtle differences between the two authentication mode, one being HBase RPC authentication other Web authenticator, and same configuration would exactly not apply by default.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example the &apos;kerberos&apos; mode at REST server would require and additional &quot;HTTP/_HOST@REALM&quot; principal be created and specified. Hence I think these two must remain decoupled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
